# Self-Service General Dashboards

This Notebook provides access to Best Practice Building Blocks for Dynatrace General Dashboards with many tile/variable examples. Scroll down for a detailed description of the Dashboard, Use Cases, Install Instructions and much more. You can download/upload any content and use the dashboard as is. Or you can take certain portions of the dashboard, remove/add content to fit your specific use case. If you are interested in building your own content from scratch within your wireframe, listed below are a few tile and variable examples to get you started.

## Operational Health
This dashboard provides a health overview for an Applications, Security, Logs, Hosts, Services, Network and Problems.

![](data:image/webp;base64,)


### Prerequisites

None.

### Target Audience

- Executive
- Line of Business
- Application Owner
- SRE

### Use Cases

- What is the overall health of Ecosystem?
- Is MTTR currently acceptable?
- Is my Network healthy and free of errors?
- Is my application easy to use and are my users achieving good experiences?
- Are my customers satisfied with their digital experiences?
- Do I have any Security exposures that need attention?
- Do I have any critical log messages that need attention?
- How are my Hosts performing?
- How are my Services performing?
- Are any of my Services failing and need attention?
 
### Install Instructions

- Click [Dashboard JSON](https://github.com/TechShady/Dynatrace-Dashboards-Gen3/blob/main/IT%20Operational%20Health.json) and select Download raw file ![](data:image/webp;base64,)
- Launch the Dashboard app
- Select Upload and select the JSON file for your download folder
- Select Review all code in the upper right hand corner of your Dashboard
- Check Always trust code in this document and then select Accept and run
- Test out you Dashboard by selecting options from the Variable dropdown list and adjusting the Dashboard timeframe
- Note: If you need to remove a Health Category (for example, you are not using Logs on GRAIL), perform the following steps:

         Remove the tile in the Health Banner (i.e. Log Health)
         Remove any times in the middle section for that category (i.e. Log Error Rate)
         Modify the Overall Health tile and remove the code between the Start/End block for that category (i.e. // Start Logs and // End Logs)

## Problem Overview Dashboard

This dashboard provides an overview of anomalies within your applications, services and infrastructure.
 
![](data:image/webp;base64,)

### Prerequisites

None.

### Target Audience

- SRE
- Developer
- Infrastructure Manager 

### Use Cases

- What is my Top problem by Event?
- What day/time did I experience an increase in Problems?
- What is my MTTR?
- Are my problems trending in a good direction?
- How many open Problems do I have?
- How many Problems have been closed today?
